  <!-- Intro Section -->
  <main>
    <section>
      <h2>Mapping Access to Public Resources in King County</h2>
      <p>
        This project explores the spatial distribution of key public resources
        across King County, Washington, including public health clinics,
        community centers, libraries, and parks. By visualizing where these
        resources are located, we aim to identify patterns of accessibility
        and potential gaps in service across neighborhoods.
      </p>

      <p>
        Access to public resources plays an important role in community
        well-being, education, public health, and overall quality of life.
        This project uses interactive web maps to highlight how access
        to these resources varies across different areas of King County.
      </p>

      <a href="map1.html">
        <button>Explore the Dashboard</button>
      </a>
    </section>
